<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-08-1424 </DOCNO><TEXT>A state-of-the-art report of current research in geothermal energy ispresented. Topics have been taken from all aspects of the field, to givea comprehensive view of the exploration, development, engineering andproduction of all types of geothermal energy, and the ways in which knowledgeand techniques have developed over the last decade. Particular topicscovered range from the formation of geothermal resources and their physicaland thermodynamic properties, geophysics and geochemistry, the practicalitiesof exploiting these resources, electric power generation, direct usesof earth heat and hot dry rock exploration.</TEXT></DOC>